comment_data.body: And now that the method takes an argument, you could even call `bound_method(42)` here and see if it does the right thing.

Yes. I encountered an obscure failure in the CI that I cannot reproduce locally after https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/2969/commits/1e2c7ee88fc6eb9b386d08642b1fdb6c81e997a5, so I am enriching the tests very incrementally to figure out what could have cause the failure. As soon as this turns green I'll add an assertion on the `method`'s result.
It's looking good now, so I'll add the assertion.

Goals:
– New version scheme: 3.x instead of 0.x.
– Change default `language_level` from `2` to `3`.
– Change default for `binding` directive from `False` to `True`.
– Fix some Python compatibility issues (if possible, allowing for breaking changes).
